      <tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>6 threads, <a href=item.html?item=2993&start=0>1</a>  page(s) long</td><td  style='font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;</td></tr></table></form><ul><table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100262293329264></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100262293329264><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=2993&mid=100262293329264>Fairly Extensive Melatite Drop Info</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=2993&mid=100262293329264#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=55740><span id= >Morokael</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Oct 9th 6:22 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I camped 15 bars of melatite for my guild. Being a Dark Elf Shadowknight, the faction hits aren't an issue. Level 42 SK, I would say fairly well equipped for my level. &gt;;-)<br><br>Faction hits from the CWGs were (all negative)...<br>-Miners Guild 628      (dorfs in Kaladim)<br>-Merchants of Ak'Anon  (gnomes in Akanon)<br>-King Ak'Anon          (gnomes in Akanon)<br>-Gemchoppers           (gnomes in Akanon)<br>-Solusek Mining Co     (gnomes in Sol A )<br><br>I'm gonna lump all the mobs together, even though they are varying levels. Low green (no xp) to high blue (good xp). Max hits ranged from 48-66, while I was keeping track. HPs ranged from about 900 to 1200. I was using 110 and 140pt dots, so it's hard to say exact numbers. The "Cs" - XC, MC, CC - cast a cold based DD (about 50pts without decent resistance, hit me for 10-20 with resist gear and resist cold buff). The "Bs" - XB, MB, CB - cast a HUGE knockback spell of trivial damage (5-10, magic based, got this down to about 3-6 with a resist magic buff). The SX is a spider. The X_ bots are the hardest, the C_ bots are the easiest. EXG popped two times off the wandering spawn otherwise it was a spider bot, (which also only spawns on the wanderer, as far as I can tell) a C_ bot or a M_ bot, usually of the "B" type. You NEED to move to the front of the little "castle" and camp there. The three spawns before the bridge are NOT sufficient for camping because of the 15-18 minute respawn time.<br><br>99 spawns to get 15 bars. that's 1/6.6 spawns. Not that rare, but it doesn't seem that way. heh. I also looted two dufrenite during my time there, I believe from Model MAs, but I didn't realize they were "special" so I just sold them in Neriak (either 10p or 19p each, heh). Made just under 500p over these 99 kills. Coin loot ranged from 0p0g0s4c to 3p6g6s10c per corpse while I kept track, the C_ bots usually dropping much more money than the harder versions. Almost all the versions of CWGs drop fine steel weapons, I assume the spiders do NOT, but with only two kills I can't prove that.<br><br>Name (# of melatite dropped) - notable loot<br><br>2xEXG (0) - 2 Charred Guardian Shields.<br>2xSX  (0) - Small and Large Power Sources.<br>36xMA (0) - nothin special (possibly Dufrenite)<br>9xMB  (3) - Broken/Complete Force Modules.<br>8xMC  (4) - Broken/Complete Frost Modules.<br>28xCA (0) - nothin special<br>3xCB  (2) - Broken/Complete Force Modules.<br>3xCC  (1) - Broken/Complete Frost Modules.<br>3xCX  (2) - clockwork oil stout<br>3xXA  (0) - nothin special<br>1xXB  (0) - assuming Broken/Complete Force Modules.<br>1xXC  (1) - assuming Broken/Complete Frost Modules.<br><br>So according to my results, I would feel secure in saying that melatite drops from "B" and "C" type mobs (the ones that cast). I would assume that they all (all 6 versions) have the same chance of dropping melatite, but given such a small sample size I wouldn't want to guess at a % chance. I seriously doubt killing the "A" types will ever get you melatite, same with the spider or EXG.<br><br>For the longest time I was furious with how difficult the Darkforge quests were, I /salute and pity you Paladins for the HORRIBLE amount of work you have to go through for your quests. They need to make melatite drop off an evil type mob in an evil zone, like say buff up the stone guardians in Neriak and have THOSE drop it, yes?<br><br>I hope this information is of some use. Until next we meet. Death before Dishonour.<br><br>Morokael Xeranus &lt;Wicked Ways&gt; Tholuxe Paells<br><a href="http://pub39.ezboard.com/bwickedways" target=_new>http://pub39.ezboard.com/bwickedways</a><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
